question:
Given a file `scores.txt` with contents:

```
John 80 90 70
Mary 85 75 95
Alex 60 70 65
```

What will the following command print?

`awk '{
	sum=0;
	for(i=2; i<=NF; i++)
		sum+=$i
	print $1, sum/(NF-1)
}' scores.txt | sort -k2 -nr | head -1`

What is the primary purpose of this AWK script?

```awk
#!/usr/bin/awk -f
{
	for(i=1; i<=NF; i++) {
		word = tolower($i)
		gsub(/[^a-z]/, "", word)
		if (word != "")
			freq[word]++
	}
}
END {
	for (word in freq) {
		printf "%-15s %d\n", word, freq[word]
	}
}
```

